wikipedia_page.main:
David John Young (born 11 December 1977) is a former English cricketer and a sport psychologist.  Young was a right-handed batsman.  He was born in Coventry, Warwickshire.
Young represented the Middlesex Cricket Board in 2 List A matches against the Derbyshire Cricket Board and Cambridgeshire in the 1st and 2nd rounds of the 2003 Cheltenham & Gloucester Trophy which were held in 2002.  In his 2 List A matches, he scored 32 runs at a batting average of 16.00, with a high score of 22.
Since playing, Young has established himself as a leading sport psychologist in the United Kingdom, working with a number of professional teams across a variety of sports
